verses.text: And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,
Send thou men , that they may search the land of Canaan , which I give unto the children of Israel : of every tribe of their fathers shall ye send a man , every one a ruler among them.
And Moses by the commandment of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* sent them from the wilderness of Paran : all those men \add \+w were|strong="H1992"\+w*\add* heads of the children of Israel.
And these \add were\add* their names : of the tribe of Reuben , Shammua the son of Zaccur.
Of the tribe of Simeon , Shaphat the son of Hori.
Of the tribe of Judah , Caleb the son of Jephunneh.
Of the tribe of Issachar , Igal the son of Joseph.
Of the tribe of Ephraim , Oshea the son of Nun.\f + \fr 13.8 \ft Oshea: also called, Joshua\f*
Of the tribe of Benjamin , Palti the son of Raphu.
Of the tribe of Zebulun , Gaddiel the son of Sodi.
Of the tribe of Joseph , \add namely\add*, of the tribe of Manasseh , Gaddi the son of Susi.
Of the tribe of Dan , Ammiel the son of Gemalli.
Of the tribe of Asher , Sethur the son of Michael.
Of the tribe of Naphtali , Nahbi the son of Vophsi.
Of the tribe of Gad , Geuel the son of Machi.

These \add are\add* the names of the men which Moses sent to spy out the land. And Moses called Oshea the son of Nun Jehoshua.\f + \fr 13.16 \ft Oshea: also called Joshua\f*\f + \fr 13.16 \ft Jehoshua: or, Joshua\f* \p
¶ And Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan , and said unto them, Get you up this \add way\add* southward , and go up into the mountain :
And see the land , what it \add is;\add* and the people that dwelleth therein, whether they \add be\add* strong or weak , few or many ;
And what the land \add is\add* that they dwell in , whether it \add be\add* good or bad ; and what cities \add they be\add* that they dwell in , whether in tents , or in strong holds ;

And what the land \add is\add*, whether it \add be\add* fat or lean , whether there be wood therein, or not. And be ye of good courage , and bring of the fruit of the land. Now the time \add was\add* the time of the firstripe grapes. \p
¶ So they went up , and searched the land from the wilderness of Zin unto Rehob , as men come to Hamath.
And they ascended by the south , and came unto Hebron ; where Ahiman , Sheshai , and Talmai , the children of Anak , \add were\add*. (Now Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)

And they came unto the brook of Eshcol , and cut down from thence a branch with one cluster of grapes , and they bare it between two upon a staff ; and \add they brought\add* of the pomegranates , and of the figs.\f + \fr 13.23 \ft brook: or, valley\f*

The place was called the brook Eshcol , because of the cluster of grapes which the children of Israel cut down from thence.\f + \fr 13.24 \ft brook: or, valley\f*\f + \fr 13.24 \ft Eshcol: that is, A cluster of grapes\f*
And they returned from searching of the land after forty days. \p

¶ And they went and came to Moses , and to Aaron , and to all the congregation of the children of Israel , unto the wilderness of Paran , to Kadesh ; and brought back word unto them, and unto all the congregation , and shewed them the fruit of the land.
And they told him, and said , We came unto the land whither thou sentest us, and surely it floweth with milk and honey ; and this \add is\add* the fruit of it.
Nevertheless the people \add be\add* strong that dwell in the land , and the cities \add are\add* walled , \add and\add* very great : and moreover we saw the children of Anak there.
The Amalekites dwell in the land of the south : and the Hittites , and the Jebusites , and the Amorites , dwell in the mountains : and the Canaanites dwell by the sea , and by the coast of Jordan.
And Caleb stilled the people before Moses , and said , Let us go up at once , and possess it; for we are well able to overcome it.
But the men that went up with him said , We be not able to go up against the people ; for they \add are\add* stronger than we.

And they brought up an evil report of the land which they had searched unto the children of Israel , saying , The land , through which we have gone to search it, \add is\add* a land that eateth up the inhabitants thereof; and all the people that we saw in it \add are\add* men of a great stature.\f + \fr 13.32 \ft men…: Heb. men of statures\f*
And there we saw the giants , the sons of Anak , \add which come\add* of the giants : and we were in our own sight as grasshoppers , and so we were in their sight.
